result.execSummary:
The defendant Crystal Lena Cornell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: To be paid in full within first 60 days of probation.
To be paid within first 60 days of probation.

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

The defendant must not possess or consume alcohol. 

The defendant must not enter into any bar or taverns.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

timeConds.notes: Community Service to be completed within first 60 days of probation.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Crystal Lena Cornell in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 9:27 am. State - has a resolution, defendant would plead to count 1, counts 2, 3 & 4 would be DRI - w/hold sentence and probation for one year - 50 hrs community service, $300 plus costs, standard probation conditions. Joy/Cornell agree. Defendant pleads to G to count 1 - court goes thru plea questionnaire and finds that defendant is entering her plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently by entering her plea and waiving her right to JT, factual basis, accepts plea and adjudges guility of count 1. Court DRI 2, 3 & 4. Joy make final argument. Cornell withholds statement. Court sentences to following: w/hold sentence and place on probation for 1 year with following conditions: 50 hrs community service to be completed within first 6 months, fine of $300 plus costs paid thru probation paid and to be paid within first 60 days, AODA, no possession or consumption of alcohol, no entry into bar or taverns, full time employment. Appeal rights.

Defendant Crystal Lena Cornell in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 2:47 p.m. State - filed information which mirrors the complaint. Joy - has handed the court waiver of preliminary hearing and waives further reading of filed information. Court goes over form and finds the defendant has freely, voluntairly and intelligently waived her right to preliminary hearing, finds probable cause and binds over for trial. Proceed to ARGN. Joy enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas and sets for FPT. Bond continues.  Final pre-trial scheduled for May 13, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
